Do you read what I actually wrote and what the point of the thread was?<br>
<br>
I am not against gay people... I am not against gay people having freaky sex.   I just don't want to be called a homophobe every time I wince at the thought of it.<br>
<br>
I did say that I like blowjobs and other forms of expressive contact with people that do not reproduce.  Yes, it does not appeal to me when two people of the same gender do that.<br>
<br>
I also said I was incorrect in calling it unnatural after someone pointed it out with other animals as the example.  Also the fact that many believe people are gay from birth, although I would not know for certian because I am not gay.<br>
<br>
Yes, I would like to be with 2 women at the same time in a sexual act and yes it is hypocritical I know. <br>
<br>
Sorry if my reasoning is faulty  and my &quot;arguement&quot; is the same.   I can never understand what it is to be gay, to have those feelings or to ever understand why?   I just know I disapprove of the act itself while still having the capacity to not disapprove of the person.    And yes your quote is pretty good as to how I feel.<br>
<br>
I hope I made things a bit more clear for you and anyone else that skimmed along like you did.<br>
<br>
