Are you saying that all gay people should move to gay neighborhoods in large cities in California and Florida, or move to Canada, just because they would be accepted there?  <br>
<br>
The problem is close minded communities overly concerned with what everyone else is doing, not the people who are &quot;different&quot; and therefore unequal.  Even the recent Supreme Court decision legalizing sodomy offended me.  To me, the case was not about Privacy, it was not about hiding in my bedroom with my boyfriend, out of mind, out of sight.  It was about Equality, and being able to walk down the street holding my boyfriend's hand, or kiss him goodbye as he gets into his car to go to work, without there being any reason for the general populace to be offended.<br>
<br>
Just my intuitive take on the issue. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=giovannifv>GiovanniFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 231<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/27/03 1:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm62.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=686.topic&index=32>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://pic7.picturetrail.com/VOL217/1032248/1929737/31981514.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: yeah another Gay thread. *try to be mature and civil*</span><hr size=1> RE: Shintou<br>
